cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.SI

The paper discusses the integration of machine learning into socially sensitive decision processes, which suggests a focus on machine learning and its applications. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the potential for perpetuating historical and contemporary socioeconomic disparities, which suggests a focus on social implications and ethics. This could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the need for fairness-aware machine learning, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
